00:00:31.331 --> 00:00:34.010
Sí.

3
00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:35.634
Why?

4
00:00:36.203 --> 00:00:39.538
Why is this still
under discussion?

5
00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:43.253
No. No. no. no.

6
00:00:43.277 --> 00:00:46.022
I don't like him.

7
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:49.258
I don't care who he knows.

8
00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:53.217
We're supposed to trust
him with our products.

9
00:00:55.923 --> 00:00:57.567
Big man.

10
00:00:57.591 --> 00:00:59.218
Big Generalissimo!

11
00:00:59.242 --> 00:01:02.555
Big fry cook is more like it.

12
00:01:02.579 --> 00:01:05.075
The "Chicken Man."

13
00:01:05.099 --> 00:01:07.744
You will do what you want.

14
00:01:07.768 --> 00:01:09.417
But you have my vote.

15
00:01:16.910 --> 00:01:19.705
Never trust a South American.

16
00:01:19.729 --> 00:01:23.260
Dirty. dirty people.

17
00:01:27.370 --> 00:01:30.750
He broke my toy!
He broke my toy!

18
00:01:30.774 --> 00:01:33.758
He was just having fun.

19
00:01:35.662 --> 00:01:37.140
You'll get over it.

20
00:01:37.164 --> 00:01:40.048
No! I hate him! I
wish he was dead!

21
00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:46.555
Whoo-hoo. Ha. ha.

22
00:01:53.981 --> 00:01:56.675
Marco.

23
00:01:56.699 --> 00:01:58.878
Sí.

24
00:01:58.902 --> 00:02:02.804
Grab your old uncle
a beer. would you?

25
00:02:06.243 --> 00:02:08.644
No. no. A cold one.

26
00:02:17.838 --> 00:02:20.116
This is what you wanted.

27
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:22.240
Your brother dead. Right?

28
00:02:25.629 --> 00:02:28.825
You're going to have
to try harder than that

29
00:02:28.849 --> 00:02:31.283
if you want to save him.

30
00:02:32.853 --> 00:02:37.133
How much longer do you
think he has down there?

31
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:40.942
One minute? Maybe
more? Maybe less?

32
00:02:57.027 --> 00:02:59.961
Family is all.

33
00:04:38.478 --> 00:04:40.690
Hey. you got nothing on me. yo.

34
00:04:40.714 --> 00:04:44.043
All right. you can call my
lawyer. Saul Goodman.

35
00:04:44.067 --> 00:04:45.862
Talk to my lawyer. all right?

36
00:04:45.886 --> 00:04:47.713
You hear me? I
got nothing to say.

37
00:04:47.737 --> 00:04:49.337
I told you. you can call my...

38
00:04:51.674 --> 00:04:53.503
Christ!

39
00:04:53.527 --> 00:04:55.137
You got my cell phone number.

40
00:04:55.161 --> 00:04:57.657
you had my wife's
name! How did you do it?

41
00:04:57.681 --> 00:05:00.164
Talk! Who you working with?

42
00:06:11.821 --> 00:06:13.204
Yes. sir.

43
00:06:22.499 --> 00:06:25.845
If. uh. you're ready to talk.

44
00:06:25.869 --> 00:06:28.330
they wanna get a statement.

45
00:06:28.354 --> 00:06:30.955
Your side of what happened here.

46
00:06:32.158 --> 00:06:35.310
Or we can hold them
off till another time.

47
00:06:39.316 --> 00:06:42.250
Maybe you wanna
talk to a lawyer.

48
00:06:52.178 --> 00:06:53.623
There it is.

49
00:06:55.014 --> 00:06:57.894
Heh. Yo. Adrian.

50
00:06:57.918 --> 00:07:01.997
Rocky called. he wants
his face back. Heh. heh.

51
00:07:02.021 --> 00:07:03.833
Come on. I gotta cheer you up.

52
00:07:03.857 --> 00:07:05.334
You see that?

53
00:07:05.358 --> 00:07:07.720
That's your
get-out-of-jail-free card.

54
00:07:07.744 --> 00:07:09.255
You understand. right?

55
00:07:09.279 --> 00:07:12.341
I mean. just blink once if
you're following. Heh. heh.

56
00:07:12.365 --> 00:07:16.279
The DEA's worst nightmare
is that face out in public.

57
00:07:16.303 --> 00:07:19.549
They'll have to steer a wide
berth of young Master Pinkman

58
00:07:19.573 --> 00:07:23.186
for fear of the PR poop storm
that will rain down on them

59
00:07:23.210 --> 00:07:27.173
if this story ever gets
out. I mean. this beating?

60
00:07:27.197 --> 00:07:29.642
Best thing for you.

61
00:07:29.666 --> 00:07:30.949
You're home free.

62
00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:34.480
Good. right?

63
00:07:34.504 --> 00:07:35.803
Right.

64
00:07:55.676 --> 00:07:57.720
Oh. my God.

65
00:07:57.744 --> 00:08:00.489
You're now officially
the cute one of the group.

66
00:08:00.513 --> 00:08:03.247
Paul. meet Ringo. Ringo. Paul.

67
00:08:06.753 --> 00:08:08.914
This is... I. uh...

68
00:08:08.938 --> 00:08:12.618
Jesse. I'm... I am
so sorry for this.

69
00:08:12.642 --> 00:08:15.310
This should not have happened.

70
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.525
But it did.

71
00:08:19.549 --> 00:08:21.783
No thanks to you.

72
00:08:25.289 --> 00:08:27.666
But the plan did work.

73
00:08:27.690 --> 00:08:29.802
We would've been
locked up right now

74
00:08:29.826 --> 00:08:32.872
if we didn't lure
him away. But this...

75
00:08:32.896 --> 00:08:35.375
This... I just...

76
00:08:35.399 --> 00:08:36.915
I never saw this coming.

77
00:08:41.772 --> 00:08:43.638
So...

78
00:08:44.908 --> 00:08:47.287
What. uh...?

79
00:08:47.311 --> 00:08:48.755
What happens now?

80
00:08:48.779 --> 00:08:50.923
What happens now?

81
00:08:50.947 --> 00:08:55.261
I'll tell you what happens now.

82
00:08:55.285 --> 00:08:59.782
Your scumbag
brother-in-law is finished.

83
00:08:59.806 --> 00:09:02.101
Done.

84
00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:03.436
You understand?

85
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:08.240
I will own him
when this is over.

86
00:09:08.264 --> 00:09:11.077
Every cent he earns.

87
00:09:11.101 --> 00:09:14.746
every cent his wife earns

88
00:09:14.770 --> 00:09:17.649
is mine.

89
00:09:17.673 --> 00:09:19.718
Anyplace he goes.

90
00:09:19.742 --> 00:09:21.920
anywhere he turns.

91
00:09:21.944 --> 00:09:24.123
I'm gonna be there.

92
00:09:24.147 --> 00:09:27.259
grabbing my share.

93
00:09:27.283 --> 00:09:32.031
He'll be scrubbing toilets
in Tijuana for pennies.

94
00:09:32.055 --> 00:09:34.500
and I'll be standing over him

95
00:09:34.524 --> 00:09:37.069
to get my cut.

96
00:09:37.093 --> 00:09:39.472
He'll see me when he
wakes up in the morning

97
00:09:39.496 --> 00:09:42.208
and when he crawls to sleep

98
00:09:42.232 --> 00:09:44.543
in whatever rat
hole is left for him

99
00:09:44.567 --> 00:09:49.048
after I shred his house down.

100
00:09:49.072 --> 00:09:53.185
I will haunt his crusty ass

101
00:09:53.209 --> 00:09:55.187
forever

102
00:09:55.211 --> 00:09:57.490
until the day

103
00:09:57.514 --> 00:10:00.959
he sticks a gun up his mouth

104
00:10:00.983 --> 00:10:03.262
and pulls the trigger

105
00:10:03.286 --> 00:10:06.354
just to get me out of his head.

106
00:10:07.690 --> 00:10:13.294
That's what happens next.

107
00:10:20.787 --> 00:10:23.583
Uh. my advice:

108
00:10:23.607 --> 00:10:26.669
That's probably
not a good strategy.

109
00:10:26.693 --> 00:10:29.038
I mean. they're
scared of you right now.

110
00:10:29.062 --> 00:10:30.889
They want nothing
to do with you.

111
00:10:30.913 --> 00:10:32.909
But if you hit them.

112
00:10:32.933 --> 00:10:35.828
they're forced to hit back hard.

113
00:10:35.852 --> 00:10:37.296
I mean. they will turn over

114
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:39.915
every rock hither.
thither and yon.

115
00:10:39.939 --> 00:10:42.185
until someone spills
the beans on you

116
00:10:42.209 --> 00:10:44.003
and anyone associated with you.

117
00:10:44.027 --> 00:10:45.571
present company included.

118
00:10:45.595 --> 00:10:48.791
Yes. I think what Saul is
saying makes a lot of sense.

119
00:10:48.815 --> 00:10:53.462
Jesse. move on with your life.

120
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.131
Leave it behind. all of it.

121
00:10:55.155 --> 00:10:57.566
Nothing changes

122
00:10:57.590 --> 00:11:00.569
once I walk out of here.

123
00:11:00.593 --> 00:11:05.196
I get myself a new RV
and go start cooking again.

124
00:11:06.466 --> 00:11:09.795
How exactly do you think

125
00:11:09.819 --> 00:11:11.797
you're going to
get away with that?

126
00:11:11.821 --> 00:11:13.449
They will catch you.

127
00:11:13.473 --> 00:11:15.485
So what? What?

128
00:11:15.509 --> 00:11:17.653
I have a
get-out-of-jail-free card.

129
00:11:17.677 --> 00:11:22.758
Hey. I may have overstated
the power of your face.

130
00:11:22.782 --> 00:11:25.478
Not this.

131
00:11:25.502 --> 00:11:28.603
If the cops catch me.

132
00:11:29.872 --> 00:11:32.873
I give them what
they want the most.

133
00:11:37.397 --> 00:11:39.013
You.

134
00:11:43.787 --> 00:11:46.365
They nab me.

135
00:11:46.389 --> 00:11:48.567
I make a deal

136
00:11:48.591 --> 00:11:53.406
to give up the great Heisenberg

137
00:11:53.430 --> 00:11:57.748
and his million-dollar
drug ring.

138
00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:04.967
You're my free pass.

139
00:12:04.991 --> 00:12:07.174
bitch.

140
00:12:12.065 --> 00:12:13.342
<i>You're so sure.</i>

141
00:12:13.366 --> 00:12:15.210
Look. if he didn't
give up my name

142
00:12:15.234 --> 00:12:17.446
while Hank was
beating him senseless.

143
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.015
he's never going to talk.

144
00:12:19.039 --> 00:12:21.517
What do you think that
was in there. a bluff?

145
00:12:21.541 --> 00:12:23.519
He wants your brother-in-law.

146
00:12:23.543 --> 00:12:25.588
There's gonna be
a parade of lawyers

147
00:12:25.612 --> 00:12:28.190
creaming their Underoos
for a case like that.

148
00:12:28.214 --> 00:12:29.926
I'd take it if it wouldn't cause

149
00:12:29.950 --> 00:12:31.460
so much collateral damage.

150
00:12:31.484 --> 00:12:33.062
And him cooking again?

151
00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:35.831
Hey. when. not
if. he gets caught.

152
00:12:35.855 --> 00:12:38.867
and he's facing 20
years. what'll he do then?

153
00:12:38.891 --> 00:12:42.037
Believe me. there's no
honor among thieves.

154
00:12:42.061 --> 00:12:45.096
Except for us. of
course. Heh. heh.

155
00:12:46.282 --> 00:12:47.793
No. he'll...

156
00:12:47.817 --> 00:12:49.917
He'll come around.

157
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:52.632
And if he doesn't.

158
00:12:52.656 --> 00:12:55.317
there may come a
time to talk options.

159
00:12:55.341 --> 00:12:56.957
Options?

160
00:13:12.258 --> 00:13:14.503
I'm convinced
Mr. Pinkman was involved

161
00:13:14.527 --> 00:13:16.638
in the manufacture
and distribution

162
00:13:16.662 --> 00:13:18.374
of phenyl-2 methamphetamine.

163
00:13:18.398 --> 00:13:20.709
specifically what
we call the blue meth.

164
00:13:20.733 --> 00:13:22.411
I tracked him to a scrap yard

165
00:13:22.435 --> 00:13:25.081
where he stored an
early-'80s camper.

166
00:13:25.105 --> 00:13:26.983
an RV.

167
00:13:27.007 --> 00:13:29.919
While waiting for a warrant
to search this vehicle.

168
00:13:29.943 --> 00:13:32.988
which I believe to
be a rolling meth lab.

169
00:13:33.012 --> 00:13:35.891
I received a telephone call

170
00:13:35.915 --> 00:13:40.929
telling me my wife Marie had
been injured in an accident.

171
00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:43.633
Upon hearing the
news. I left Mr. Pinkman

172
00:13:43.657 --> 00:13:47.369
and his vehicle
to tend to my wife.

173
00:13:47.393 --> 00:13:48.838
Arriving at the hospital.

174
00:13:48.862 --> 00:13:51.107
I learned the emergency
call was a hoax.

175
00:13:51.131 --> 00:13:54.693
My wife. fortunately.
was unharmed.

176
00:13:57.153 --> 00:13:59.798
So I immediately went
back to the salvage yard.

177
00:13:59.822 --> 00:14:01.701
but the RV was gone.

178
00:14:01.725 --> 00:14:04.153
Most likely destroyed on site.

179
00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.488
And it was at this point

180
00:14:05.512 --> 00:14:07.629
you drove to the home
of Jesse Pinkman?

181
00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:21.286
I think we're done here.

182
00:14:21.310 --> 00:14:24.073
Agent Schrader
needs to get home.

183
00:14:24.097 --> 00:14:25.274
get some rest.

184
00:14:25.298 --> 00:14:27.426
That's fine. But
just to confirm.

185
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:30.262
you're taking the Fifth here?

186
00:14:30.286 --> 00:14:31.947
Yeah. that's correct.

187
00:14:31.971 --> 00:14:33.933
Okay. Well.

188
00:14:33.957 --> 00:14:36.902
we just wanna give
you all a heads up.

189
00:14:36.926 --> 00:14:40.489
Mr. Pinkman is pressing
charges in this matter.

190
00:14:40.513 --> 00:14:44.860
He's given a detailed version
of events as he sees them.

191
00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:46.345
The word of a meth head.

192
00:14:46.369 --> 00:14:48.197
We know all about his history.

193
00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:51.655
We're well aware. but
toxicology on Pinkman...

194
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:55.437
His blood is clean.
he's not using.

195
00:14:55.461 --> 00:14:58.707
The kid is even refusing
his doctor-ordered pain meds.

196
00:14:58.731 --> 00:15:00.548
far as we can tell.

197
00:15:03.219 --> 00:15:04.786
So. um...

198
00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:08.634
where do we go from here?

199
00:15:08.658 --> 00:15:11.437
A couple of gentlemen
from OPR will come down.

200
00:15:11.461 --> 00:15:13.472
probably tomorrow morning.

201
00:15:13.496 --> 00:15:15.808
Janice will give us
an exact time on that.

202
00:15:15.832 --> 00:15:21.613
And you men will be continuing
your investigation. so...

203
00:15:21.637 --> 00:15:25.150
Thanks for your
time. Right. We just...

204
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:27.203
We need one more thing.

205
00:15:27.227 --> 00:15:31.128
A photo of Agent Schrader's
hands. For the record.

206
00:15:32.548 --> 00:15:34.560
Yes. of course.

207
00:15:34.584 --> 00:15:36.967
Bandage off. if you would.

208
00:15:42.392 --> 00:15:45.487
On the table is fine.

209
00:15:45.511 --> 00:15:47.828
Flat on the table. That's fine.

210
00:17:28.514 --> 00:17:30.292
It's all gonna work out.

211
00:17:30.316 --> 00:17:33.662
You've been too good to
them for too many years.

212
00:17:33.686 --> 00:17:35.764
I hope it goes without saying

213
00:17:35.788 --> 00:17:39.489
we're not talking to
anybody about this. okay?

214
00:17:40.827 --> 00:17:42.326
Okay.

215
00:17:44.396 --> 00:17:47.915
Marie. who?

216
00:18:22.535 --> 00:18:23.695
Hi.

217
00:18:23.719 --> 00:18:26.181
Do you have a minute?

218
00:18:26.205 --> 00:18:28.155
Sure.

219
00:18:42.721 --> 00:18:45.022
I guess crime does pay.

220
00:18:49.228 --> 00:18:52.696
I don't suppose you
just came by to insult me.

221
00:18:54.867 --> 00:18:58.364
No. We need to talk.

222
00:18:58.388 --> 00:19:00.866
You heard about Hank?

223
00:19:00.890 --> 00:19:04.770
About what happened with
this. um. Jesse Pinkman?

224
00:19:04.794 --> 00:19:07.222
Yes. I know.

225
00:19:07.246 --> 00:19:09.625
Whatever Hank was investigating.

226
00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:13.678
him trying to find an RV.

227
00:19:13.702 --> 00:19:15.614
is there any danger

228
00:19:15.638 --> 00:19:18.183
that could lead back to you?

229
00:19:18.207 --> 00:19:20.752
No.

230
00:19:20.776 --> 00:19:22.342
Why would it?

231
00:19:26.098 --> 00:19:28.032
Is this why you're here?

232
00:19:29.869 --> 00:19:31.536
I'm here to talk about Hank.

233
00:19:33.473 --> 00:19:35.434
You know what's
gonna happen to him

234
00:19:35.458 --> 00:19:38.692
if this Pinkman presses charges?

235
00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:43.413
Hank could lose everything.

236
00:19:46.452 --> 00:19:48.452
I thought maybe. um.

237
00:19:50.489 --> 00:19:53.302
there's a way you
could help him.

238
00:19:53.326 --> 00:19:55.170
How?

239
00:19:55.194 --> 00:19:58.173
Contact Pinkman.

240
00:19:58.197 --> 00:19:59.908
Get him to drop the charges.

241
00:19:59.932 --> 00:20:02.911
Look. Skyler. I don't know
what kind of relationship

242
00:20:02.935 --> 00:20:05.180
you picture me
having with this person.

243
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:06.315
I'm not asking.

244
00:20:06.339 --> 00:20:09.485
He was... He's...
He's not my friend.

245
00:20:09.509 --> 00:20:11.653
It's not as if we
were even close.

246
00:20:11.677 --> 00:20:14.340
I'm... I'm not asking.

247
00:20:14.364 --> 00:20:17.693
But there must be
something you could say.

248
00:20:17.717 --> 00:20:21.029
Isn't it even worth a try?

249
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:23.353
Hank is your family.

250
00:20:26.626 --> 00:20:28.336
Not currently.

251
00:20:28.360 --> 00:20:29.888
What?

252
00:20:29.912 --> 00:20:32.379
I said. not currently.

253
00:20:33.849 --> 00:20:36.917
I'm late. I have to go.

254
00:21:09.451 --> 00:21:10.695
Hello.

255
00:21:10.719 --> 00:21:13.720
I was starting to get worried.

256
00:21:15.391 --> 00:21:16.990
Car trouble.

257
00:21:18.093 --> 00:21:19.943
Oh. that's a bummer.

258
00:21:21.330 --> 00:21:24.176
You should call me
next time. I'll pick you up.

259
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.299
Uh-huh.

260
00:21:27.403 --> 00:21:31.566
No sandals today?

261
00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:33.173
I just thought...

262
00:21:34.259 --> 00:21:37.272
A bit more professional.

263
00:21:37.296 --> 00:21:40.447
Well. everything is on track.

264
00:21:42.685 --> 00:21:45.197
We got our distillate.
Just waiting to...

265
00:21:45.221 --> 00:21:47.332
Let's get our trays ready.

266
00:21:47.356 --> 00:21:49.068
Clean. no moisture.

267
00:21:49.092 --> 00:21:50.092
Done.

268
00:21:53.412 --> 00:21:56.058
Is our. uh...?

269
00:21:56.082 --> 00:21:57.693
Our solvent filtered?

